name: Androscoggin
nyt_race_description_race: Maine is only one of two states where there is no winner-take-all of the Electoral College votes. As in Nebraska, the winner in each Maine district (there are two) receives one Electoral College vote in a process called the congressional district method. So there is a scenario in which the presidential election could be decided by a vote in Maine. That might be in this increasingly competitive race, where the Republican challenger Dale Crafts hopes to unseat Jared Golden, the incumbent Democrat and a Marine Corps veteran.
poll_display_race: Polls close at 8 p.m. Eastern time.
